{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779203536285,"sessionID":"ses_1bf3887f0ffe2434yrKINYlsHp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_00_Qdwr8sjMQelxdVo56pXw4310","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/status/CONTRACT_VALIDATION.md","oldString":"mismatches_found: 4\n\n## Mismatches\n\n| DTO | Field | Backend Expects | Frontend Sends | Severity |\n|-----|-------|-----------------|----------------|----------|\n| LoginDto | password | min 8 chars (`PROJECT_API.md` — `/auth/login`) | min 6 chars (`frontend/app/utils/validations/auth.ts:5`) | HIGH |\n| CreatePropertyDto | address | flat fields: `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, `addressState`, `addressZipCode` (`backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts:48-58`) | nested object: `{street, city, state, zipCode}` (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:4-11`, `frontend/app/pages/admin/property-form.tsx:28-33`) | MEDIUM |\n| PropertySearchParams | sortBy | `sortBy: string` + `sortOrder: 'ASC' \\| 'DESC'` (`backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts:28-36`) | combined: `'price_asc' \\| 'price_desc' \\| 'newest' \\| 'oldest'` (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:70`) | MEDIUM |\n| InquiryFilters | sortBy | same `sortBy` + `sortOrder` pattern from `PaginationDto` | `'newest' \\| 'oldest'` (`frontend/app/types/api/inquiry.d.ts:67`) | MEDIUM |\n\n### Mismatch Details\n\n#### 1. Login password min length (HIGH)\n- **Backend contract** (`PROJECT_API.md`): password requires \"min 8 chars\"\n- **Frontend validation** (`frontend/app/utils/validations/auth.ts:4-5`):\n  ```ts\n  password: z.string().min(6, \"Password must be at least 6 characters\"),\n  ```\n- **Impact**: Users can submit passwords of length 6-7 characters that pass frontend validation but will be rejected by the backend with a 400 error.\n\n#### 2. Property address structure (MEDIUM)\n- **Backend entity** (`backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts:48-64`):\n  ```ts\n  @Column({ name: 'address_street', ... }) addressStreet: string;\n  @Column({ name: 'address_city', ... })  addressCity: string;\n  @Column({ name: 'address_state', ... }) addressState: string;\n  @Column({ name: 'address_zip_code', ... }) addressZipCode: string;\n  @Column({ name: 'address_latitude', ... }) addressLatitude: number | null;\n  @Column({ name: 'address_longitude', ... }) addressLongitude: number | null;\n  ```\n- **Frontend DTO** (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:4-11`) and form (`frontend/app/pages/admin/property-form.tsx:28-33`):\n  ```ts\n  address: {\n    street: string;\n    city: string;\n    state: string;\n    zipCode: string;\n    latitude?: number;\n    longitude?: number;\n  }\n  ```\n- **Impact**: The frontend sends a nested `address` object, but the backend entity stores address fields as flat columns. A DTO transformer would be needed on the backend to map between these structures, or the frontend needs to flatten the address fields.\n\n#### 3. Property search sortBy convention (MEDIUM)\n- **Backend PaginationDto** (`backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts:28-36`):\n  ```ts\n  sortBy?: string;        // field name, e.g. 'createdAt'\n  sortOrder?: 'ASC' | 'DESC';  // direction\n  ```\n- **Frontend PropertySearchParams** (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:70`):\n  ```ts\n  sortBy?: 'price_asc' | 'price_desc' | 'newest' | 'oldest';\n  ```\n- **Impact**: The frontend combines field and direction into a single string value (`price_asc`), while the backend expects them as two separate parameters. The frontend values won't be recognized by the backend's intended sort system.\n\n#### 4. Inquiry sortBy convention (MEDIUM)\n- **Same root cause as #3**: `InquiryFilters.sortBy` uses `'newest' | 'oldest'` (`frontend/app/types/api/inquiry.d.ts:67`) instead of the backend's separate `sortBy` + `sortOrder` pattern from `PaginationDto`.\n- **Impact**: Same as mismatch #3 — different sort parameter conventions.","newStrin